Hello. Team 554 here. We are experiencing an issue/bug in Pathplanner where when the end of a path is reached, the swerve modules (Turning Motors) start spinning randomly at end of path. We need some help fixing this!

Issue in More Detail:
When the end of path is reached, and we are executing a Named Command, Wait Command, or another path, the Swerve Modules are rotating at a random rate. The turning motors are spinning with zero velocity on the drive motors. The waypoints between paths are linked together. Autobuilder being used to create the auto command. We expect that when the path ends, no wheel movement would occur before the next path begins or when running a named command or wait command with no motion, but this is not what is happening. We are seeing other local teams experiencing the same issue, so I’m not sure if anyone else out there has found a fix for this issue. Some chiefdelphi forums talk about adding a stop modules command at the end of a path, but that doesnt logically make sense. Any help would be great as this motion is causing our shots to be missed. Thanks so much for the help!

You might want to check the heading on your end points. Here’s an example where I was able to make a little weird jiggle at the end of a path.
In path 1, the heading is on the wrong side, so the path jiggles at the end:

When this is combined with another path in a auto, you can see it has a little “bounce” right at that point.
